Q1. Best Value Item (Ratings / Price)
You are given two arrays of equal length:
â€¢	prices[] â€” the price of each item
â€¢	ratings[] â€” the rating of each item (from 1 to 5)
Each index represents the same item in both arrays.
Find the index of the item that has the highest ratio of rating / price.
If multiple items have the same highest ratio, return the one with the smallest index.
________________________________________
ðŸ“¥ Input
â€¢	prices: array of positive integers
â€¢	ratings: array of positive integers
Constraints
â€¢	1 â‰¤ prices.length â‰¤ 100
â€¢	1 â‰¤ prices[i] â‰¤ 100
â€¢	1 â‰¤ ratings[i] â‰¤ 5
â€¢	prices.length == ratings.length
________________________________________
ðŸ“¤ Output
â€¢	Return an integer â€” the index of the item with the highest rating / price value.
________________________________________
ðŸ§ª Example 1
Input
prices = [6, 5, 4, 3]
ratings = [4, 3, 2, 1]
Calculations
4 / 6 â‰ˆ 0.66
3 / 5 = 0.60
2 / 4 = 0.50
1 / 3 â‰ˆ 0.33
Output
0
________________________________________
ðŸ§ª Example 2
Input
prices = [7, 5, 2, 11]
ratings = [3, 4, 1, 3]
Calculations
3 / 7 â‰ˆ 0.43
4 / 5 = 0.80
1 / 2 = 0.50
3 / 11 â‰ˆ 0.27
Output
1
________________________________________
âœ… Notes
â€¢	You are not required to optimize heavily.
â€¢	A simple loop comparing ratios is sufficient.
â€¢	If two ratios are equal, return the smaller index.

Solution:
import java.util.*;

class Main {
    
    public static int getMaxPItem(int[] ratings,int[] price) {
        double max_item = -1;
        int idx=0;

        for(int i=0;i<ratings.length;i++) {
            double score = (double) ratings[i]/price[i];

            if(max_item < score) {
                max_item = score;
                idx=i;
            }
        }

        return idx;
    }
    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        int[] ratings = new int[n];
        int[] price = new int[n];

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            ratings[i] = sc.nextInt();
        } 

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            price[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int res = getMaxPItem(ratings,price);
        System.out.println(res);
    }
}
